  "nursesNote": "Mental illness affects the whole family, who often experience stress, grief, and caregiver burden. With the patient's consent (respecting confidentiality), the nurse educates the family about the illness and treatment, teaches how to communicate and respond to symptoms calmly and supportively, and teaches the warning signs of relapse so they can act early. The nurse reduces stigma and blame, reassuring the family that the illness is not their fault. Families are connected to support groups (such as NAMI), respite care, and community resources, and are involved in the care and discharge plan. The nurse assesses for caregiver burden and burnout (stress, exhaustion, isolation) and encourages caregiver self-care so support is sustainable.",
  "providerOrders": [
    "Educate the family about the illness and treatment (with consent)",
    "Teach how to respond to symptoms and warning signs of relapse",
    "Reduce stigma and reassure the family it is not their fault",
    "Connect to support groups, respite, and resources",
    "Assess caregiver burden and encourage self-care"
  ],
